============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is supply and demand?
A1: Supply and demand determines prices: higher demand or
     lower supply raises prices; lower demand or higher
     supply lowers prices. Equilibrium is where both curves
     intersect.

Q2: What is osmosis?
A2: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q3: What is evolution?
A3: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q4: What is gravity?
A4: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q5: What is relativity?
A5: Einstein's relativity: Special (1905) — time dilates,
     mass increases at high speeds; E=mc². General (1915) —
     gravity is curved spacetime; explains black holes and
     expanding universe.

